org.ensembl.datamodel
Interface MarkerFeature

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable, Feature, Locatable, Persistent, java.io.Serializable
public interface MarkerFeature
extends Feature

Represents a marker feature in the EnsEMBL database. A marker feature is the location where a marker has been mapped to the genome by ePCR.

Author:
Craig Melsopp

getDisplayName

public java.lang.String getDisplayName()
This method returns a string that is considered to be the 'display' identifier. For marker features this is the name of the display synonym or '' if it is not defined.
